      • fireZoneExitedEvent

        protected void fireZoneExitedEvent(Entity entity)
        Overrides Zone.fireZoneExitedEvent(Entity) to push a ChatZoneExitedEvent to the event bus. Note that listeners for ZoneExitedEvent will still be notified, but will need to cast the event.

        Unlike fireZoneExitedEvent(Entity, String), no exit message is provided; as such, the message field will simply be left null in the resulting ChatZoneExitedEvent.

        Overrides:
        fireZoneExitedEvent in class Zone
        Parameters:
        entity - the entity that exited the zone
        See Also:
        Zone.removeEntity(Entity)

      • fireZoneExitedEvent

        protected void fireZoneExitedEvent(Entity entity,
                       String message)
        This fires a ChatZoneExitedEvent containing an optional exit message. Entities may be removed from the zone with a message by calling removeEntity(Entity, String). The message may be null, as is the case when the ordinary Zone.removeEntity(Entity) is called.
        Parameters:
        entity - the entity that left the zone
        message - the zone exit message, if any
        See Also:
        removeEntity(Entity, String)
